    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Typical Frisian money chests given by a husband to his fiancée during an engagement ritual. These are usually small and rectangular and are often made of silver. The surface of the chest is usually decorated or engraved and sometimes contains a text.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
